---
import Signpost from "../signpost/signpost.astro";
---

<section class="what">
  <h2>What are the rules</h2>
  <p>11 rules. 5 areas. Each with a constraint, rationale and code example.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <h3><a href="/skill#architecture">Architecture</a></h3>
      <p>
        Manage specificity with <code>@layer</code>, encapsulated styles with <code
          >@scope</code
        >, nesting with <code>&amp;</code> and relational styles with <code
          >:has()</code
        >
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3><a href="/skill#typography">Typography</a></h3>
      <p>
        Fluid type sizes with <code>clamp()</code>, and text wrapping with <code
          >text-wrap: balance</code
        > and <code>pretty</code>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3><a href="/skill#colors">Colors</a></h3>
      <p>
        Perceptually uniform lightness with <code>oklch()</code>, color scheme
        support with <code>light-dark()</code>, and relative colors
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3><a href="/skill#layout">Layout</a></h3>
      <p>
        Container queries and units, intrinsic sizing with <code
          >fit-content</code
        > and <code>max-content</code>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <h3><a href="/skill#motion">Motion</a></h3>
      <p>
        Respecting motion preferences with <code
          >prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference</code
        >
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <Signpost href="/skill">Read the full rules</Signpost>
</section>
